==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[berige|beriġe]], from Germanic ''*basjon'' (apparently ‘grape’), of unknown ultimate origin.  Cognate with Dutch [[bes]], German [[Beere]].
 
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈbɛri/}}
*{{AHD|bĕ'ri}}, {{SAMPA|/"bEri/}}
*:'''Homophones''': [[bury]]
*{{audio|en-us-berry.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛri|-ɛri]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|berr|ies}}

#A small [[fruit]], of any one of many varieties.
#A soft fruit which [[develop]]s from a [[superior]] [[ovary]] and contains [[seed]]s not encased in [[pit]]s.

